<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<task id="AIPU-051" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Dark Mode and NFR Verification for All 17 Output and Source Widgets</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <wave>5</wave>
    <estimated-effort>6 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>testing, fluent-ui</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>AIPU-020, AIPU-021, AIPU-022, AIPU-031, AIPU-032</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Write automated tests that verify all 17 output and source widgets (11 output widgets + 6 source
    widgets) satisfy the dark mode and NFR requirements. Tests focus exclusively on:
    - NFR-01: Widget renders within 200ms in both light and dark themes.
    - NFR-04: Widget renders correctly under webDarkTheme without visual breakage.
    - ADR-021: No hard-coded color strings in widget source files (verified by static analysis).
    Tests are added as new .test.tsx files in the Spaarke.AI.Outputs library test folder. No
    production code is modified in this task.
  </prompt>

  <role>QA/test developer experienced with React Testing Library, Fluent UI v9 FluentProvider
  theming, and performance timing assertions.</role>

  <goal>All 17 widgets (11 output + 6 source) have corresponding dark mode and render-time tests
  that pass. A static scan confirms no hard-coded color values exist in widget source files.
  Test files live in src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/**/*.test.tsx.</goal>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/source-widgets/</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/__tests__/</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/source-widgets/__tests__/</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/package.json</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/jest.config.ts</file>
    <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r1/spec.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <constraints>
    <constraint id="ADR-021">All widget source files must use Fluent v9 semantic color tokens
    only. Hard-coded color strings (e.g. "#ffffff", "rgb(", "rgba(", named CSS colors not from
    Fluent tokens) are forbidden. The static scan in this task makes this requirement testable.
    </constraint>
    <constraint id="NFR-01">Each widget must render to the DOM within 200ms when given minimal
    mock props. Measure with performance.now() or Jest fake timers around the render call.
    </constraint>
    <constraint id="NFR-04">Each widget must render without throwing errors under webDarkTheme.
    Verify by wrapping the render in FluentProvider theme={webDarkTheme} and asserting the
    component mounts successfully and contains expected structural elements.</constraint>
    <constraint id="test-files-only">This task MUST NOT modify any production widget source files.
    Only new .test.tsx files and supporting test utilities may be created. If a widget fails a
    test due to a hard-coded color or theme issue, record the failure — do not fix the widget
    source in this task (that is a production code change requiring a separate task).</constraint>
    <constraint id="no-snapshot-sprawl">Do not use snapshot tests. Use targeted assertions:
    getByRole, getByText, or container.querySelector for structural checks. Snapshot tests create
    maintenance burden and do not verify semantic correctness.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/guides/ai-assistant-theming.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/theme-consistency.md</file>
      <file>docs/architecture/AI-ARCHITECTURE.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>Dark mode test harness pattern:
      import { render } from "@testing-library/react";
      import { FluentProvider, webDarkTheme, webLightTheme } from "@fluentui/react-components";

      function renderWithTheme(ui: React.ReactElement, theme = webLightTheme) {
        return render(&lt;FluentProvider theme={theme}&gt;{ui}&lt;/FluentProvider&gt;);
      }

      it("renders in dark mode without error", () => {
        const { container } = renderWithTheme(&lt;MyWidget {...mockProps} /&gt;, webDarkTheme);
        expect(container.firstChild).toBeTruthy();
      });
      </pattern>
      <pattern>Render time assertion pattern:
      it("renders within 200ms", () => {
        const start = performance.now();
        renderWithTheme(&lt;MyWidget {...mockProps} /&gt;);
        const elapsed = performance.now() - start;
        expect(elapsed).toBeLessThan(200);
      });
      </pattern>
      <pattern>Static color scan — run from test or as a separate script:
      grep -rn --include="*.tsx" --include="*.ts" -E '(#[0-9a-fA-F]{3,6}|rgb\(|rgba\(|color:\s*"[a-z])'
      src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/
      Any match that is not from a Fluent token import is a violation.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read spec.md to identify the full list of 11 output widgets and 6 source widgets
    with their names and mock prop requirements. Read existing widget source files in
    src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/ and source-widgets/ to understand
    each widget's props interface.</step>
    <step id="2">Create a shared test utility file at
    src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/__tests__/test-utils.tsx: export renderWithTheme
    helper (wraps render in FluentProvider), export mockOutputItem and mockSourceItem factory
    functions that produce minimal valid props for each widget type.</step>
    <step id="3">For each of the 11 output widgets, create a test file at
    src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/output-widgets/__tests__/{WidgetName}.test.tsx with:
    (a) a light theme render test confirming it mounts without error,
    (b) a dark theme render test (webDarkTheme) confirming it mounts without error,
    (c) a render time test asserting completion within 200ms.</step>
    <step id="4">For each of the 6 source widgets, create a test file at
    src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/source-widgets/__tests__/{WidgetName}.test.tsx
    with the same three test cases as step 3.</step>
    <step id="5">Create a static color scan test at
    src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs/src/__tests__/no-hardcoded-colors.test.ts: using Node's
    fs module and a regex pattern, scan all .tsx and .ts files in the output-widgets/ and
    source-widgets/ directories for hard-coded color strings. The test fails and reports the
    offending file and line number for each match.</step>
    <step id="6">Run the full test suite: cd src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Outputs &amp;&amp; npx jest.
    Record which tests pass and which fail. For any failures, note whether the failure is in the
    test setup (fixable in this task) or in the production widget (record as a finding — do not
    fix production code).</step>
    <step id="7">Document all widget test failures (if any) in a findings comment at the top of
    the relevant test file, formatted as: "FINDING: Widget uses hard-coded color #XXXX at
    {file}:{line}. Requires production fix in separate task."</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion id="AC-1">Test files exist for all 17 widgets: 11 in output-widgets/__tests__/
    and 6 in source-widgets/__tests__/.</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-2">Each widget test file contains at minimum 3 tests: light theme render,
    dark theme render, and render time under 200ms.</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-3">The shared test-utils.tsx provides renderWithTheme and mock prop
    factories used consistently across all widget tests.</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-4">The no-hardcoded-colors.test.ts static scan test exists and executes.
    If it finds violations, they are recorded as FINDING comments in the relevant test files.
    </criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-5">npx jest runs to completion (no test infrastructure errors). All test
    failures are documented as FINDING comments rather than unexplained errors.</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-6">No production widget source files (*.tsx outside __tests__/) are
    modified by this task.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
